From: Bart Van Assche <bvanassche@acm.org>
Date: Mon, 4 Mar 2024 15:57:15 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] fs/aio: Check IOCB_AIO_RW before the struct aio_kiocb
 conversion
References: bsc#1218260
Patch-mainline: 6.6.24
Git-commit: 961ebd120565cb60cebe21cb634fbc456022db4a

commit 961ebd120565cb60cebe21cb634fbc456022db4a upstream.

The first kiocb_set_cancel_fn() argument may point at a struct kiocb
that is not embedded inside struct aio_kiocb. With the current code,
depending on the compiler, the req->ki_ctx read happens either before
the IOCB_AIO_RW test or after that test. Move the req->ki_ctx read such
that it is guaranteed that the IOCB_AIO_RW test happens first.

